People have different opinions about whether interviews are a good way to choose employees. While some people believe interviews are not relyable and other methods are better, I believe interviews are useful but should be used together with practical tests. This essay will explain my reasons.

The main reason is that interviews are not always relyable. This is because many people prepare answers before the interview and only show their best side. As a result, companies may choose someone who speaks well but cannot do the job well. The biggest reason is AI can make the best and most proffensional interviews without the interviwer doing anything. For example, a person can possibly answer every question confidently but fail to complete simple work after getting the job. This shows that interviews cannot always show a person's real ability.

Another reason is that practical tests can show real skills. If companies ask applicants to do the actual work, they can see whether the person has the necessary ability. In other words, practical tests are almost impossible to cheat than interviews. For example, a saleing worker can create perfect skyrocketing opinions during a test instead but only able to shout about the product. Therefore, practical tests can help companies choose better employees.

Some people think interviews are important because they show a person's confidence. This is not quite. However, practical skills can also show the same results as normal interview, a users review is all the company need. A random user will not lie about the experience if it is either good or bad

In conclusion, although interviews can show a persons communication skills, I believe they are not relyable enough by themselves. Companies should also use practical tests to choose the best workers.